1
00:00:47,291 --> 00:00:50,291
<i>AN ACTOR PREPARES</i>

2
00:00:56,916 --> 00:00:59,250
- Is it an accident?
- What happened?

3
00:00:59,333 --> 00:01:00,708
- I'll go and see.
- Let's take a look.

4
00:01:00,833 --> 00:01:02,166
- Is everything all right?
- He fainted.

5
00:01:02,250 --> 00:01:04,166
- Hurry.
- That's not good.

6
00:01:04,708 --> 00:01:08,166
- Sir, where are you hurting?
- It hurts.

7
00:01:08,833 --> 00:01:11,166
- Where?
- I don't know. Everywhere.

8
00:01:11,666 --> 00:01:13,833
- Let me help you get up.
- I can't move. It's too painful.

9
00:01:13,916 --> 00:01:15,083
- He is here.
- Is it there?

10
00:01:15,166 --> 00:01:17,416
Is this a scam? Is it real?

11
00:01:17,666 --> 00:01:19,500
- Hello, is this emergency service?
- It must be fake.

12
00:01:19,708 --> 00:01:20,958
- I'm here at Dapeng.
- Is it a scam?

13
00:01:21,041 --> 00:01:22,041
Is it real?

14
00:01:22,125 --> 00:01:23,083
Sir.

15
00:01:23,958 --> 00:01:25,291
I'm also an actor.

16
00:01:25,833 --> 00:01:27,208
Your acting is not good.

17
00:01:27,458 --> 00:01:29,375
{\an8}The key to a scam is the feeling of pain.

18
00:01:29,458 --> 00:01:31,791
You're not showing enough emotion.
It's not convincing enough.

19
00:01:31,916 --> 00:01:33,291
- Gosh.
- Look at you.

20
00:01:33,541 --> 00:01:34,875
Even your moan is so frivolous.

21
00:01:34,958 --> 00:01:37,583
You were hit by a car.
You can't just moan like that.

22
00:01:37,708 --> 00:01:38,875
Of course, you can't succeed.

23
00:01:38,958 --> 00:01:41,958
Otherwise, the audiences
won't sympathize with you.

24
00:01:42,458 --> 00:01:44,125
Gosh. It really hurts.

25
00:01:44,958 --> 00:01:48,041
No, sir. Your acting is terrible.

26
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:49,416
Let me show you.

27
00:01:50,208 --> 00:01:51,375
Gosh.

28
00:01:52,666 --> 00:01:53,708
It hurts...

29
00:01:54,125 --> 00:01:56,041
Sir, you're doing it too fast.

30
00:01:56,125 --> 00:01:58,375
Fainting is fine, but it has a process.

31
00:01:58,458 --> 00:02:00,541
For example, hold onto your head...

32
00:02:01,625 --> 00:02:03,208
The blood looks real.

33
00:02:03,458 --> 00:02:05,500
Too bad your acting was bad
in the beginning.

34
00:02:05,583 --> 00:02:07,833
You've already lost your credibility.

35
00:02:08,625 --> 00:02:10,375
I'm just sharing some tips with you.

36
00:02:10,458 --> 00:02:12,083
Don't take it personally, sir.

37
00:02:12,458 --> 00:02:13,416
The ambulance is here.

38
00:02:13,791 --> 00:02:16,333
- Make way.
- Make way.

39
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:20,791
Mild fracture in the left chest,
third rib bone, not life-threatening.

40
00:02:20,875 --> 00:02:21,708
Come on.

41
00:02:21,791 --> 00:02:23,000
That's so serious.

42
00:02:23,208 --> 00:02:24,083
Hurry.

43
00:02:26,333 --> 00:02:27,791
- Ready, up.
- Up.

44
00:02:28,958 --> 00:02:30,375
- Be careful.
- Okay.

45
00:02:32,291 --> 00:02:34,000
I'm so sorry, sir.

46
00:02:34,208 --> 00:02:35,500
Is the lady his family member?

47
00:02:35,708 --> 00:02:37,125
She is a lunatic. Ignore her.

48
00:02:41,250 --> 00:02:42,416
What happened?

49
00:02:43,166 --> 00:02:44,375
- Help.
- Help.

50
00:02:44,958 --> 00:02:46,375
- Help!
- My leg!

51
00:02:48,708 --> 00:02:50,333
Hey, what the hell are you doing?

52
00:02:50,416 --> 00:02:51,541
Don't you know how to act?

53
00:02:52,125 --> 00:02:54,541
You're in pain. Why aren't you screaming?
Do you know how to act?

54
00:02:54,625 --> 00:02:56,375
Well, in my own experience,

55
00:02:56,583 --> 00:02:58,916
when people are in pain,
they don't always scream out loud.

56
00:02:59,083 --> 00:03:00,416
What the hell are you talking about?

57
00:03:01,208 --> 00:03:02,458
Sir, please come over.

58
00:03:02,875 --> 00:03:04,750
Could you act out a painful reaction?

59
00:03:07,375 --> 00:03:08,416
This is fake.

60
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:09,708
Do me a favor.

61
00:03:17,250 --> 00:03:19,041
This is real. There is no sound, right?

62
00:03:19,125 --> 00:03:20,333
Please talk to the director.

63
00:03:21,250 --> 00:03:23,208
Director, what do you think?

64
00:03:23,791 --> 00:03:24,958
- I...
- Director?

65
00:03:25,291 --> 00:03:26,583
You...

66
00:03:26,791 --> 00:03:27,791
- Three.
- Three.

67
00:03:28,291 --> 00:03:29,333
Get the hell out.

68
00:03:29,958 --> 00:03:30,875
What happened?

69
00:03:30,958 --> 00:03:32,875
- She was thrown out.
- Thrown out?

70
00:03:34,291 --> 00:03:35,708
- What happened to her?
- Who knows.

71
00:03:35,791 --> 00:03:37,583
- I don't know.
- What's happening?

72
00:03:38,583 --> 00:03:40,333
- Hey!
- He is here.

73
00:03:41,166 --> 00:03:44,125
I need an extra to play as a corpse.
You must keep the makeup on for two days.

74
00:03:44,208 --> 00:03:45,833
- Who wants to go?
- How much?

75
00:03:45,916 --> 00:03:47,083
It's 400 dollars for two days.

76
00:03:47,166 --> 00:03:48,791
- Add more.
- That's too little. Add some more.

77
00:03:48,875 --> 00:03:49,750
I'll go.

78
00:03:49,875 --> 00:03:51,375
Can I play a role that can show my face?

79
00:03:51,583 --> 00:03:52,666
Are you bargaining with me?

80
00:03:52,750 --> 00:03:54,208
You don't have to pay me. A meal is fine.

81
00:03:54,291 --> 00:03:55,833
- Okay. Let's go.
- Is she doing it for free?

82
00:03:55,916 --> 00:03:57,208
She is crazy.

83
00:03:57,291 --> 00:03:58,791
- Yes.
- There's something wrong with her.

84
00:04:49,708 --> 00:04:51,916
Come on, let's eat.
The food is getting cold.

85
00:04:53,416 --> 00:04:55,083
Gosh. It's your birthday today.

86
00:04:55,166 --> 00:04:58,041
If you don't start eating,
no one else will.

87
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:00,708
Dad.

88
00:05:01,416 --> 00:05:02,458
Happy birthday.

89
00:05:02,625 --> 00:05:04,125
- Happy birthday.
- Happy birthday.

90
00:05:08,541 --> 00:05:11,375
Dreamy, your makeup is very unique today.

91
00:05:11,541 --> 00:05:12,625
It's quite terrifying.

92
00:05:13,041 --> 00:05:14,333
Is filming fun?

93
00:05:14,958 --> 00:05:16,333
I get to play a corpse this time.

94
00:05:16,416 --> 00:05:18,750
There's a close-up,
so I can show my acting skills.

95
00:05:19,666 --> 00:05:21,958
How could you even show
your acting skills by playing a corpse?

96
00:05:22,041 --> 00:05:26,291
Dad, death makes
an interesting context for actors.

97
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:27,375
Imagine.

98
00:05:27,666 --> 00:05:30,125
If you were to die now
and your whole body turns stiff...

99
00:05:30,208 --> 00:05:31,750
What did you say?
I dare you to say it again.

100
00:05:31,875 --> 00:05:34,250
Birthdays should be a happy occasion.

101
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:36,083
Dreamy, stop the nonsense.

102
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:37,708
Go and remove your makeup.

103
00:05:38,125 --> 00:05:39,583
But I still have a shoot tomorrow.

104
00:05:39,708 --> 00:05:41,583
Do you really think
you're a famous movie star?

105
00:05:42,666 --> 00:05:44,083
You guys grew up together, right?

106
00:05:44,375 --> 00:05:47,000
Look at Bobby.
He is now a big-time lawyer.

107
00:05:47,791 --> 00:05:49,500
It's nothing much. Nothing to brag about.

108
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:51,791
And look at Peggy.
She lives a happy life now.

109
00:05:51,875 --> 00:05:53,333
She married a good husband.

110
00:05:53,583 --> 00:05:55,000
Look at you.

111
00:05:55,208 --> 00:05:57,458
We'd hoped you would become a lawyer.

112
00:05:57,916 --> 00:05:59,666
Not a corpse.

113
00:05:59,875 --> 00:06:01,375
Everyone has their own specialty.

114
00:06:01,541 --> 00:06:03,708
A lawyer and a corpse make no distinction.

115
00:06:03,833 --> 00:06:06,125
I can support myself even if I'm an extra.

116
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:07,916
I have my own dreams too.

117
00:06:08,083 --> 00:06:09,291
You're already 30 years old.

118
00:06:09,375 --> 00:06:11,291
You've been an extra for over a decade.

119
00:06:11,666 --> 00:06:12,833
Have you ever played the lead?

120
00:06:12,916 --> 00:06:14,875
I believe that with my talents,

121
00:06:14,958 --> 00:06:17,625
if I work hard,
I can definitely be the lead actress.

122
00:06:18,916 --> 00:06:19,875
Sorry.

123
00:06:20,833 --> 00:06:23,791
- Mom, do you believe in me?
- Yes, you can do it.

124
00:06:24,250 --> 00:06:25,375
That's bullshit!

125
00:06:25,833 --> 00:06:27,416
It's all your fault. You've spoiled her!

126
00:06:28,083 --> 00:06:30,333
I'm giving you one last chance.

127
00:06:30,875 --> 00:06:32,625
Take that thing off your head!

128
00:06:33,416 --> 00:06:34,625
I can't.

129
00:06:34,791 --> 00:06:36,291
Then, I'll add one more for you.

130
00:06:39,416 --> 00:06:40,416
Here. You asked for it.

131
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:41,625
Wait a second.

132
00:06:41,791 --> 00:06:42,750
Never mind.

133
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:44,000
Your emotions are so inspiring.

134
00:06:44,083 --> 00:06:45,416
Dad, hold the cleaver and hop again.

135
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:46,666
I want to record this.

136
00:06:46,791 --> 00:06:48,166
Ready, jump.

137
00:06:48,291 --> 00:06:49,750
- You've gone too far.
- Gosh.

138
00:06:50,416 --> 00:06:51,833
Look at her.

139
00:06:51,916 --> 00:06:53,500
- What are you doing?
- Aunt, we'll leave now.

140
00:06:53,583 --> 00:06:55,041
- I'm sorry.
- Get out.

141
00:06:58,125 --> 00:06:59,583
I've never given birth to you!

142
00:07:01,916 --> 00:07:04,041
Take your trash with you.

143
00:07:05,583 --> 00:07:08,333
But Dad, those are all your trash.

144
00:07:08,541 --> 00:07:10,083
I don't give a damn.

145
00:07:10,875 --> 00:07:12,791
You total bum.

146
00:07:13,125 --> 00:07:14,625
Get the hell out of here.

147
00:07:14,958 --> 00:07:16,708
Enough.

148
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:18,333
Stop it.

149
00:07:18,541 --> 00:07:19,958
It's all your fault.

150
00:07:20,208 --> 00:07:21,291
Enough!

151
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:23,708
Hey!

152
00:07:23,791 --> 00:07:25,125
Can anyone act here?

153
00:07:25,208 --> 00:07:27,083
- Yes.
- I can.

154
00:07:27,166 --> 00:07:28,041
Hey, you. Show me.

155
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:29,500
Do a happy reaction.

156
00:07:29,875 --> 00:07:30,791
A sad reaction.

157
00:07:31,125 --> 00:07:32,000
All right, come with me.

158
00:07:32,208 --> 00:07:33,750
Hey, who can do an angry look?

159
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:34,666
- Me.
- Me.

160
00:07:34,750 --> 00:07:35,583
You.

161
00:07:36,875 --> 00:07:37,833
No way. Get lost.

162
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:38,750
You try.

163
00:07:39,916 --> 00:07:41,083
Okay, come along.

164
00:07:41,333 --> 00:07:43,500
Anyone, act like you've got hit
by the ultimate power.

165
00:07:43,583 --> 00:07:45,166
- Me.
- You try.

166
00:07:45,666 --> 00:07:47,875
Director, can you specify
the type of the move?

167
00:07:47,958 --> 00:07:50,500
What's with all the questions?
Get lost if you can't do it.

168
00:07:50,666 --> 00:07:52,833
- How about Icy Palm Attack?
- Okay, Icy Palm Attack.

169
00:08:01,333 --> 00:08:02,291
It's so cold.

170
00:08:03,666 --> 00:08:04,791
It's freezing.

171
00:08:06,916 --> 00:08:10,833
Go see a doctor if you're sick.
I don't want to get infected.

172
00:08:11,541 --> 00:08:12,375
You. Try.

173
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:14,416
Why are you dragging me here?
I'm not going.

174
00:08:14,625 --> 00:08:15,916
I just want to bring her some soup.

175
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,583
You made soup for her?
Are you on her side?

176
00:08:19,083 --> 00:08:21,250
You can just pretend
we're passing by to see her.

177
00:08:21,375 --> 00:08:22,666
If I see her, I'm going to hit her.

178
00:08:22,875 --> 00:08:24,000
Don't stop me.

179
00:08:24,166 --> 00:08:25,583
- Or else, I'll hit you too.
- Idiot.

180
00:08:26,041 --> 00:08:27,916
You're asking for it.

181
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,416
What's wrong with you?

182
00:08:30,041 --> 00:08:32,250
Just do the acting.
Why do you need to know everything?

183
00:08:32,416 --> 00:08:34,000
It's you every time.

184
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:36,083
I just want to build up my character.

185
00:08:36,166 --> 00:08:37,750
Build my ass.

186
00:08:37,875 --> 00:08:39,291
No one will even notice you.

187
00:08:39,416 --> 00:08:40,916
Do you think you are the lead?

188
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:43,125
Even if I give you the context,
would you even get it?

189
00:08:43,208 --> 00:08:45,833
If you could get it,
you won't be just an extra here.

190
00:08:46,250 --> 00:08:47,666
Go, come with me!

191
00:08:47,916 --> 00:08:50,000
- That was intense.
- Yes, indeed.

192
00:08:55,666 --> 00:08:57,125
- Hello.
- What is it?

193
00:08:57,375 --> 00:08:58,958
- Could you speak nicely?
- What?

194
00:08:59,375 --> 00:09:02,708
The actor was just asking you a question,
why would you get mad at her?

195
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:04,125
What does that have to do with you?

196
00:09:04,291 --> 00:09:06,583
She is so serious about acting.
Can't you see that?

197
00:09:07,208 --> 00:09:09,750
- Who's that?
- You know who I'm talking about!

198
00:09:10,041 --> 00:09:11,416
God is watching what you're doing.

199
00:09:11,541 --> 00:09:12,708
Be careful of the karma.

200
00:09:12,791 --> 00:09:14,666
You have some nerves.
Production assistant!

201
00:09:15,291 --> 00:09:16,333
I'm sorry.

202
00:09:16,666 --> 00:09:17,541
Let's go.

203
00:09:18,791 --> 00:09:20,500
- Do you know who I am?
- No.

204
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:21,833
That's good.

205
00:09:22,541 --> 00:09:25,250
What a lunatic.

206
00:09:29,958 --> 00:09:30,875
Hello.

207
00:09:31,208 --> 00:09:33,333
Your acting for Icy Palm Attack
was intensely sensational.

208
00:09:33,416 --> 00:09:34,708
It hit the mark.

209
00:09:35,541 --> 00:09:36,583
It was passable.

210
00:09:37,083 --> 00:09:38,375
The key is imagination.

211
00:09:38,625 --> 00:09:41,000
Immerse yourself into the scene.

212
00:09:41,583 --> 00:09:42,416
That's amazing.

213
00:09:42,583 --> 00:09:43,416
I'm Young.

214
00:09:43,666 --> 00:09:44,750
I'm Dreamy.

215
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:47,625
- You're reading this book too?
- Yes.

216
00:09:48,625 --> 00:09:49,958
Do you like "King of Comedy" too?

217
00:09:50,041 --> 00:09:51,541
Of course. I love it so much.

218
00:09:51,708 --> 00:09:52,833
Do you want to try acting?

219
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,791
- Right here?
- Sure.

220
00:09:58,541 --> 00:09:59,416
Hey.

221
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:02,708
What is it?

222
00:10:02,875 --> 00:10:03,708
Are you leaving?

223
00:10:04,083 --> 00:10:04,916
Yes.

224
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,625
- Where are you going?
- Home.

225
00:10:06,958 --> 00:10:08,708
- And then?
- Off to work.

226
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:10,916
Can you not go to work?

227
00:10:11,041 --> 00:10:12,625
Are you going to feed me if I don't work?

228
00:10:19,333 --> 00:10:20,208
Hey.

229
00:10:23,166 --> 00:10:24,125
What now?

230
00:10:29,750 --> 00:10:30,958
I'll feed you.

231
00:10:35,333 --> 00:10:36,833
My boyfriend is here.

232
00:10:37,125 --> 00:10:38,875
Hey, that's the wrong line.

233
00:10:39,583 --> 00:10:42,291
No, my boyfriend is really here.

234
00:10:45,625 --> 00:10:46,458
See you.

235
00:10:48,208 --> 00:10:49,083
Who's that guy?

236
00:10:49,291 --> 00:10:50,958
- A colleague.
- Really?

237
00:10:51,041 --> 00:10:52,750
Yes. Let's go.

238
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:14,333
You can have my sausage.

239
00:11:16,791 --> 00:11:17,791
Let's share it.

240
00:11:25,458 --> 00:11:27,041
I've earned 4,000 dollars this month.

241
00:11:27,708 --> 00:11:29,458
Let's deposit it into our wedding fund.

242
00:11:29,875 --> 00:11:31,583
You only make 5,000 dollars
at most a month.

243
00:11:31,666 --> 00:11:33,666
How would you survive
if you give me 4,000 dollars?

244
00:11:34,083 --> 00:11:35,625
One thousand dollars is enough for me.

245
00:11:35,833 --> 00:11:37,583
I have free catered meals for casts.

246
00:11:37,666 --> 00:11:39,958
Let me contribute 4,500 dollars.
You can take 500 dollars.

247
00:11:41,125 --> 00:11:43,833
Take it easy. We agreed to half each.

248
00:11:44,750 --> 00:11:46,541
I thought my love for you was deeper.

249
00:11:46,958 --> 00:11:48,875
But it turns out,
your love for me is just as deep.

250
00:11:52,416 --> 00:11:53,833
Are you really giving him your money?

251
00:11:54,041 --> 00:11:54,875
Yes.

252
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,208
Then, why don't you give it to me?

253
00:11:56,291 --> 00:11:57,833
I'm not getting married to you.

254
00:11:58,750 --> 00:12:00,375
You might as well be with me then.

255
00:12:00,791 --> 00:12:02,500
- Lend me your soap.
- Okay.

256
00:12:08,583 --> 00:12:11,333
Why do you keep staring at Mimi?
Do you like her?

257
00:12:11,416 --> 00:12:13,125
It pisses me off when you say that.

258
00:12:13,208 --> 00:12:14,583
Looking at her doesn't mean I like her.

259
00:12:14,666 --> 00:12:16,750
I despise her from the bottom of my heart.

260
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:18,125
She is so cheap.

261
00:12:18,333 --> 00:12:19,791
Don't you think Mimi's pretty?

262
00:12:19,875 --> 00:12:21,125
Beauty means nothing.

263
00:12:21,208 --> 00:12:22,458
She is just an eye candy.

264
00:12:23,583 --> 00:12:25,833
