598
00:27:42,541 --> 00:27:44,500
- Who's Marco?
- It's Marco.

599
00:27:44,583 --> 00:27:46,083
- Who?
- Never mind.

600
00:27:46,291 --> 00:27:48,958
He was in a bad mood.
He kicked away my lunch box.

601
00:27:49,041 --> 00:27:51,666
So, I asked for another lunchbox,
but they refused.

602
00:27:51,833 --> 00:27:54,666
But suddenly, when I was leaving,
he gave me one.

603
00:27:54,750 --> 00:27:57,708
Does this mean good luck
is coming on my way?

604
00:27:57,791 --> 00:28:00,166
You're just an extra,
don't think too much.

605
00:28:00,250 --> 00:28:01,750
Have some respect for extras.

606
00:28:01,833 --> 00:28:04,208
Many stars started as extras.

607
00:28:04,291 --> 00:28:06,791
Sun Li, Carina Lau, Zhao Liying.

608
00:28:06,875 --> 00:28:08,166
Are you as talented as they are?

609
00:28:08,250 --> 00:28:09,458
We're all special in our own ways.

610
00:28:09,583 --> 00:28:11,000
I work harder than they do.

611
00:28:11,083 --> 00:28:12,166
I don't know what to say.

612
00:28:12,250 --> 00:28:15,375
Anyway, opportunities are reserved
for the hardworking people.

613
00:28:15,458 --> 00:28:19,500
It's impossible that I would be discovered
just by standing on the streets, right?

614
00:28:19,875 --> 00:28:20,833
Excuse me, miss.

615
00:28:22,041 --> 00:28:23,416
Would you like to be in a movie?

616
00:28:23,875 --> 00:28:24,916
Who are you?

617
00:28:25,250 --> 00:28:26,583
She is a famous producer.

618
00:28:26,791 --> 00:28:28,416
Hi, I'm Dreamy. I'm an actor.

619
00:28:28,666 --> 00:28:31,166
Hi, we're looking for actors in our movie.

620
00:28:31,291 --> 00:28:32,625
Are you interested?

621
00:28:32,708 --> 00:28:34,000
Yes, I want to try.

622
00:28:34,583 --> 00:28:36,416
Sorry, it's not you.

623
00:28:36,500 --> 00:28:37,416
It's you.

624
00:28:38,458 --> 00:28:39,958
- Me?
- Yes.

625
00:28:41,250 --> 00:28:43,833
Give it a try?
Our company is just over there.

626
00:29:12,041 --> 00:29:13,083
No worries.

627
00:29:13,375 --> 00:29:15,000
At least, you tried.

628
00:29:15,375 --> 00:29:16,541
Don't be sad.

629
00:29:16,750 --> 00:29:18,791
They picked me as the female lead.

630
00:29:19,541 --> 00:29:20,416
Really?

631
00:29:21,208 --> 00:29:23,416
I don't know how to act.
Why would they pick me?

632
00:29:23,833 --> 00:29:26,375
I went in and they removed my makeup.
I only said two lines.

633
00:29:26,458 --> 00:29:29,125
Then, I am chosen. What should I do now?

634
00:29:29,208 --> 00:29:31,750
What do you mean?
It's a great opportunity.

635
00:29:31,833 --> 00:29:34,750
If it were me, I would trade
50 years of my life for this chance.

636
00:29:35,041 --> 00:29:36,583
But I don't want it.

637
00:29:36,666 --> 00:29:40,041
I'm so scared.
I don't want to be an actor.

638
00:29:44,166 --> 00:29:45,458
It's okay.

639
00:29:45,958 --> 00:29:47,041
Don't cry.

640
00:29:47,583 --> 00:29:49,250
I'm so innocent.

641
00:29:49,500 --> 00:29:51,916
I can't let
the entertainment industry ruin me.

642
00:29:53,458 --> 00:29:55,083
I don't mind to be ruined.

643
00:29:55,250 --> 00:29:57,791
Perhaps you can recommend me to them.

644
00:29:57,875 --> 00:29:59,208
I've already told them.

645
00:29:59,500 --> 00:30:03,458
I asked them to let you in,
but they said they would rather die.

646
00:30:03,791 --> 00:30:05,000
They would rather die?

647
00:30:05,208 --> 00:30:07,958
Yes, they said they would rather die.

648
00:30:10,166 --> 00:30:11,708
- They would rather die.
- What should I do?

649
00:30:11,791 --> 00:30:14,041
- Mr. Huang from Hong Kong was here today.
- The car is over there.

650
00:30:14,125 --> 00:30:15,958
Okay. Is everything fine?

651
00:30:16,041 --> 00:30:17,666
- Don't worry. Everything is ready.
- Hi.

652
00:30:17,916 --> 00:30:20,250
- You're still here?
- Thank you for giving me the chance.

653
00:30:20,416 --> 00:30:22,041
- Do your best.
- Sure.

654
00:30:22,125 --> 00:30:23,166
Do you want a ride?

655
00:30:23,250 --> 00:30:24,625
Sure, I live nearby.

656
00:30:29,875 --> 00:30:31,083
Take the back seat.

657
00:30:45,208 --> 00:30:47,083
Mimi move out so soon?

658
00:30:48,833 --> 00:30:50,250
She has moved everything.

659
00:30:51,375 --> 00:30:53,958
She even took my soap and sanitary pads.

660
00:30:55,833 --> 00:30:57,458
I've told you.

661
00:30:57,875 --> 00:30:58,750
She is cheap.

662
00:31:01,125 --> 00:31:04,000
I shouldn't have asked Mimi
to eat with me.

663
00:31:04,500 --> 00:31:06,500
If I had gone there myself,

664
00:31:06,958 --> 00:31:08,833
they would have picked me.

665
00:31:09,125 --> 00:31:12,333
Even without Mimi,
they might not have picked you.

666
00:31:17,125 --> 00:31:19,500
Aren't opportunities reserved
for the hardworking people?

667
00:31:20,333 --> 00:31:24,208
It means that the opportunity
wasn't meant for you, but for Mimi.

668
00:31:24,375 --> 00:31:27,833
But if she doesn't try her best,
she will eventually screw up.

669
00:31:28,125 --> 00:31:31,125
Hang in there. You'll get the chance.

670
00:31:36,791 --> 00:31:39,750
You're right. I'll try even harder.

671
00:31:40,791 --> 00:31:43,333
I'll send out my CV all over China.

672
00:31:43,583 --> 00:31:46,833
I want everyone to know
what acting actually means.

673
00:31:46,916 --> 00:31:48,166
Well said.

674
00:31:48,375 --> 00:31:50,083
Be positive.

675
00:31:50,208 --> 00:31:53,583
I'm short on cash for my start-up,
but I still have hope.

676
00:31:53,708 --> 00:31:55,541
- How much do you need?
- Twenty thousand dollars.

677
00:31:56,125 --> 00:31:58,708
- How about you use the wedding fund?
- No.

678
00:31:58,833 --> 00:32:00,875
If so, we would never get married.

679
00:32:01,083 --> 00:32:03,416
Maybe I can work overtime
or get a part-time job.

680
00:32:03,500 --> 00:32:05,916
Don't worry. Just do your part well.

681
00:32:06,083 --> 00:32:07,500
Otherwise, I will feel bad.

682
00:32:15,208 --> 00:32:17,083
- Get to work.
- Lighting department, hurry.

683
00:32:17,666 --> 00:32:18,750
Help me to deliver that.

684
00:32:19,250 --> 00:32:21,250
Sir.

685
00:32:21,458 --> 00:32:22,875
- I have one here.
- Okay.

686
00:32:24,291 --> 00:32:25,458
- Excuse me.
- Add three more.

687
00:32:25,833 --> 00:32:29,166
Sir, I need money.
Do you have any work that pays more?

688
00:32:29,250 --> 00:32:31,125
Pay more? Who do you think you are?

689
00:32:31,333 --> 00:32:33,458
I can do anything.
I'm not picky about jobs.

690
00:32:33,666 --> 00:32:35,166
- What is this?
- Help me. Please.

691
00:32:35,500 --> 00:32:36,583
Thank you.

692
00:32:47,208 --> 00:32:50,041
Are you kidding me?

693
00:32:52,333 --> 00:32:55,958
Go away. I don't know what you're saying.

694
00:32:56,750 --> 00:32:58,875
Who hired the double?

695
00:33:00,083 --> 00:33:03,125
I beg you, miss. Please put on clothes.

696
00:33:04,291 --> 00:33:05,916
- Get out.
- She is scary.

697
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:08,708
Sorry, Director. I didn't know
she'd look so bad without clothes.

698
00:33:08,791 --> 00:33:11,583
Are you kidding?
Where do you find this kind of people?

699
00:33:11,875 --> 00:33:14,416
Bad figure and saggy skin.

700
00:33:14,500 --> 00:33:16,500
- She even has black stains on her ass.
- Sorry, Director.

701
00:33:16,583 --> 00:33:18,541
You might as well ask me to do it.

702
00:33:18,958 --> 00:33:20,875
- Go get me another one.
- Dreamy.

703
00:33:21,625 --> 00:33:22,750
Are you okay?

704
00:33:23,375 --> 00:33:24,375
I'm fine.

705
00:33:24,666 --> 00:33:27,125
The director said I have
a bad figure and saggy skin.

706
00:33:27,208 --> 00:33:28,750
They begged me to put my clothes on.

707
00:33:28,916 --> 00:33:30,083
I am really fine.

708
00:34:08,791 --> 00:34:12,541
{\an8}HIRING STUNT DOUBLE
HIRING EXTRAS FOR DROWNING SCENE

709
00:34:34,958 --> 00:34:35,916
Come, hurry up.

710
00:34:45,583 --> 00:34:46,750
Don't touch her.

711
00:34:46,958 --> 00:34:49,083
Everyone, do it again
in the same angle. Okay!

712
00:34:54,750 --> 00:34:55,791
Ready!

713
00:34:56,166 --> 00:34:57,083
Start!

714
00:35:28,375 --> 00:35:29,916
- Are you ready?
- In a minute.

715
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:30,916
- Director.
- Let me do this.

716
00:35:31,125 --> 00:35:33,041
Do I need to move later?

717
00:35:33,125 --> 00:35:35,000
Damn it. Have you ever seen
a moving statue?

718
00:35:35,083 --> 00:35:36,750
- No.
- Why don't you use real statues?

719
00:35:36,833 --> 00:35:38,916
Because they're too expensive. Get lost.

720
00:35:39,250 --> 00:35:40,875
- Here.
- He is here.

721
00:35:41,833 --> 00:35:44,250
Dreamy, are there any acting tips
to be a statue?

722
00:35:45,083 --> 00:35:47,916
I see. Meditating to appear lifeless.

723
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:49,000
I'll try this.

724
00:35:53,083 --> 00:35:56,208
- Everyone, stand by.
- Hurry. Let's begin.

725
00:35:56,291 --> 00:36:00,041
This scene is about the prince waking up
and realizes that Snow White is a man.

726
00:36:00,875 --> 00:36:01,791
Rolling.

727
00:36:02,541 --> 00:36:03,583
Shot Four. Take One.

728
00:36:16,291 --> 00:36:17,291
Who are you?

729
00:36:18,750 --> 00:36:20,250
I'm Snow White.

730
00:36:21,125 --> 00:36:22,333
Did I sleep with you?

731
00:36:29,916 --> 00:36:31,333
What are you doing?

732
00:36:32,041 --> 00:36:34,958
It's only lust for you, but love for me.
Why are you so upset?

733
00:36:45,166 --> 00:36:47,000
Director, get someone
to explain the scene to him.

734
00:36:47,250 --> 00:36:49,666
Come on. Let's do the close-up
of me killing him first.

735
00:36:52,875 --> 00:36:55,750
- Mr. Marco, do you know your lines?
- Stop the nonsense. It's late!

736
00:36:55,833 --> 00:36:56,750
Okay, ready.

737
00:36:59,875 --> 00:37:00,791
What's the line?

738
00:37:02,291 --> 00:37:06,166
"It's all the fault of my body.
You heartless man."

739
00:37:06,250 --> 00:37:07,166
Okay, again.

740
00:37:08,125 --> 00:37:09,708
It's all the fault of...

741
00:37:11,375 --> 00:37:12,500
Whose fault is it?

742
00:37:13,625 --> 00:37:16,750
- "It's all the fault of my body.
- "It's all the fault of my body.

743
00:37:16,833 --> 00:37:18,416
- You heartless man."
- You heartless man."

744
00:37:18,500 --> 00:37:19,666
I got it. Okay.

745
00:37:21,583 --> 00:37:23,708
<i>It's all the fault...</i>

746
00:37:24,500 --> 00:37:26,541
<i>of my boobs.</i>

747
00:37:28,125 --> 00:37:30,583
Sorry, Mr. Marco. It should be "body."

748
00:37:30,916 --> 00:37:32,041
It's the same.

749
00:37:32,500 --> 00:37:34,833
It's just a bit off.
The audience will understand.

750
00:37:35,041 --> 00:37:38,541
We have a lot of underage audiences,
it'd better be pronounced accurately.

751
00:37:38,625 --> 00:37:40,250
Kids don't care about pronunciation.

752
00:37:40,458 --> 00:37:42,750
